\title{NWQS: Non-Linear Weighted Quantile Sum Regression}
\description{
Fits non-linear weighted quantile sum (NWQS) regression models for assessing the joint effect and relative importance of correlated mixture exposures. Extends classical WQS by incorporating natural cubic splines to capture non-linear dose-response relationships (e.g., threshold, U-shaped, S-shaped curves). Supports Gaussian, binomial, Poisson, quasi-Poisson, and negative binomial families. Provides repeated holdout estimation, external bootstrap inference, permutation-based variable importance, and publication-quality diagnostic plots.
